<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1152] Option rerunFailingTestsCount silently fails with test suites</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1152</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After a test failure (with &lt;tt&gt;rerunFailingTestsCount &amp;gt; 0&lt;/tt&gt;), the &lt;tt&gt;JUnit4*Provider.executeWithRerun&lt;/tt&gt; calls &lt;tt&gt;execute&lt;/tt&gt; again with a list of the failing &lt;tt&gt;testMethods&lt;/tt&gt;, but &lt;tt&gt;JUnit4*Provider.execute&lt;/tt&gt; silently fails to find the requested methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When &lt;tt&gt;testClass&lt;/tt&gt; is actually a test suite class, it may not contain any methods at all (other than inherited &lt;tt&gt;java.lang.Object&lt;/tt&gt; methods).  The &lt;tt&gt;execute&lt;/tt&gt; method iterates through the &lt;tt&gt;java.lang.Object&lt;/tt&gt; methods, never finds a match for the &lt;tt&gt;testMethods&lt;/tt&gt;, and silently fails to execute anything.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12819942">SUREFIRE-1152</key>
