                            <comment id="14716384" author="tibor17" created="Thu, 27 Aug 2015 09:42:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Current snapshot version has incomplete LazyTestSet implementation. It needs to be cachable. Without caching tests the rerun feature would not work properly. I have a fix in my local project which is part of larger feature &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-580&quot; title=&quot;Allow &amp;quot;fail fast&amp;quot; or stop running on first failure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-580&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-580&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The feature already works and supports reusable forks. So I need two days to support all three forking strategies, writing documentation and IT and sanity checks.&lt;br/&gt;
Then a deep testing of current features like rerun, test filtering (-Dtest=%regex&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;.*Test.*&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, includes/excludes) should continue.&lt;/p&gt;

